15 Section 2. KRS 304.12-230 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) It is an unfair claims settlement practice for any insurer[person] to commit or
17 perform any of the following acts or omissions:
18 (a)[(1)] Misrepresenting pertinent facts or insurance policy provisions relating to
19 coverages at issue;
20 (b)[(2)] Failing to acknowledge and act reasonably promptly upon
21 communications with respect to claims arising under insurance policies;
22 (c)[(3)] Failing to adopt and implement reasonable standards for the prompt
23 investigation of claims arising under insurance policies;
24 (d)[(4)] Refusing to pay claims without conducting a reasonable investigation
25 based upon all available information;
26 (e)[(5)] Failing to affirm or deny coverage of claims within a reasonable time
27 after proof of loss statements have been completed;
Page 3 of 29
XXXX 2/12/2026 8:46 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1132
1 (f)[(6)] Not attempting in good faith to effectuate prompt, fair, and equitable
2 settlements of claims in which liability has become reasonably clear;
3 (g)[(7)] Compelling insureds to institute litigation to recover amounts due under
4 an insurance policy by offering substantially less than the amounts ultimately
5 recovered in actions brought by the[such] insureds;
6 (h)[(8)] Attempting to settle a claim for less than the amount to which a
7 reasonable person[man] would have believed he or she was entitled by
8 reference to written or printed advertising material accompanying or made
9 part of an application;
10 (i)[(9)] Attempting to settle claims on the basis of an application which was
11 altered without notice to, or knowledge or consent of, the insured;
12 (j)[(10)] Making claims payments to insureds or beneficiaries not accompanied
13 by a statement setting forth the coverage under which the payments are being
14 made;
15 (k)[(11)] Making known to insureds or claimants a policy of appealing from
16 arbitration awards in favor of insureds or claimants for the purpose of
17 compelling them to accept settlements or compromises less than the amount
18 awarded in arbitration;
19 (l)[(12)] Delaying the investigation or payment of claims by requiring an insured,
20 claimant, or the physician of either to submit a preliminary claim report and
21 then requiring the subsequent submission of formal proof of loss forms, both
22 of which submissions contain substantially the same information;
23 (m)[(13)] Failing to promptly settle claims, where liability has become reasonably
24 clear, under one (1) portion of the insurance policy coverage in order to
25 influence settlements under other portions of the insurance policy coverage;
26 (n)[(14)] Failing to promptly provide a reasonable explanation of the basis in the
27 insurance policy in relation to the facts or applicable law for denial of a claim
